				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10797539#post-4200113</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10797539/scp-4235#post-4200113</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 28 Mar 2019 19:33:01 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Jakuwoski</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3382837</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I didn’t know SCP-4469 and only after your mention I read this article. Maybe at first sight can look similar, because both objects are abnormally durable, but the mechanism associated is very different; in the case of the toy it cause a weakening of intermolecular forces of objects around it, which increase the fragility of this objects, while the effect associated to the rose is a “deviation of entropy”, impeding that the object to deteriorate or withering but increasing in return the entropic decay in the objects and organisms around it (i.e. the “aging” of these)</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
