					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10797539#post-4197815</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10797539/scp-4235#post-4197815</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 26 Mar 2019 19:36:56 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>fieldstone</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1436137</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It seems like a really unreliable and kind of silly way to assassinate someone, and anyway the guy in the story buys them for himself (from Marshall <em>personally</em>, no less).</p> <p>And while MC&amp;D might conceivably sell roses that don't wither but basically poison everything around them, they probably wouldn't do so without telling the customer about it. That would be a batshit insane business practice for a top secret company that relies on the super wealthy; their reputation is their most important asset.</p> <p>Obviously I'm in the minority based on the article's rating, but this just seems poorly thought out to me.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
